      },
      "date": "2013-02-02 10:24:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nPatch looks reasonable.\n\nPlease file a bug to add a couple of tests:\n- create a few thousand remote directories in one parent and do an \"\\ls -l | wc -l\" to see that they are all present.  This could be done as part of sanity.sh test_24v(), since it lists the directory already, but doesn't count the entries.  It looks like \"createmany\" needs a \"-i\" argument to specify the MDT index for DNE.\n- a new test image like conf-sanity.sh test_32(), that mounts the test MDT/OST filesystems as $FSTYPE after they have data in them, and verify some of the namespace and objects are accessible",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
